%% Mermaid Diagram %%
---
title: Contribution Decision Flow
---

flowchart TD
    AA[Start] --> AB{influence a direction?}
    AB -- Yes --> AC{defining requirements?}
    AC -- Yes --> AD[Contribution is Requirements Document]
    AC -- No  --> AE{Are you providing real world evidence?}
    AE -- Yes --> AF[Contribution is Case Study]
    AE -- No  --> AG[Contribution is White Paper]
    AB -- No  --> AH{Producing Standards or Guidance?}
    AH -- Yes --> AI{Standards?}
    AI -- Yes --> AJ{product focused?}
    AJ -- Yes --> AK[Contribution is Product Spec]
    AJ -- No  --> AL{Design focused?}
    AL -- Yes --> AM[Contribution is Design Spec]
    AL -- No  --> AN[Contribution is Base Spec]
    AI -- No  --> AO{creating blueprint?}
    AO -- Yes --> AP[Contribution is a Reference Architecture]
    AO -- No  --> AQ[Contribution is a guideline]
    AH -- No  --> AS{Design/Implementation?}
    AS -- Yes --> AT{modeling, Construction, and analysis?}
    AT -- No  --> AU{HW?}
    AU -- Yes --> AV[Contribution is a Design Package]
    AU -- No  --> AW[Contribution is Source Code]
    AT -- Yes --> AX[Contribution is Tools]
    AS -- No  --> AY{Validated Deployments?}
    AY -- Yes --> AZ[Contribution is Tested Configuration]
    AY -- No  --> BA{Real-world reference point?}
    BA -- Yes --> BB[Contribution is a Benchmark]
    BA -- No  --> BC[Contribution is Errata]